# LDREAS Researcher Portal — Design System Rules

Any development, modification, or extension to this codebase **MUST** adhere strictly to every rule below.
Violations will cause visual and functional inconsistencies across the portal.

---

## 1. Core Aesthetic

| Principle        | Rule                                                                                                      |
|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Style**        | Premium, clean, high-contrast **academic print-editorial** aesthetic (inspired by MIT, Stanford portals).  |
| **Geometry**     | Sharp corners **ONLY**. `--radius: 0px` / Tailwind `rounded-none` on **ALL** elements — buttons, cards, badges, inputs, selects, tables, dialogs, sheets, dropdowns, images, and toasts. |
| **Shadows**      | Minimal or none. Cards and panels use `shadow-sm` or `shadow-none`. No drop-shadow, no box-shadow larger than `shadow-sm`. |
| **Borders**      | Thin `1px` borders using `border-border` (HSL `220 13% 88%`). Double borders or decorative borders are **forbidden**. |
| **Animations**   | Subtle and fast only. `transition-colors duration-150` or `transition-all duration-200`. No bouncing, no slide-in, no spring animations. Spinners use `animate-spin` with a `border-2 border-primary border-t-transparent` CSS spinner — never an SVG spinner. |

---

## 2. Color Palette (CSS Custom Properties)

All colors are defined as HSL values in `src/styles/global.css` inside `:root`. They are consumed via Tailwind's `bg-*`, `text-*`, `border-*` utilities.

| Token                    | HSL Value            | Usage                                              |
|--------------------------|----------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| `--background`           | `0 0% 100%`         | Page background, input backgrounds                   |
| `--foreground`           | `220 14% 10%`       | Primary text, active sidebar tab background           |
| `--primary`              | `211 100% 35%`      | Academic Blue `#0056B3`. Buttons, links, ring focus   |
| `--primary-foreground`   | `0 0% 100%`         | Text on primary-colored elements                     |
| `--secondary`            | `220 14% 96%`       | Muted panel backgrounds, hover fills                  |
| `--secondary-foreground` | `220 14% 10%`       | Text on secondary backgrounds                        |
| `--muted`                | `220 14% 96%`       | Disabled/placeholder backgrounds                     |
| `--muted-foreground`     | `220 9% 40%`        | Secondary text, labels, timestamps                   |
| `--accent`               | `211 100% 97%`      | Light accent highlight background                    |
| `--accent-foreground`    | `211 100% 35%`      | Text on accent backgrounds                           |
| `--destructive`          | `0 84% 60%`         | Delete buttons, error states                         |
| `--destructive-foreground`| `0 0% 100%`        | Text on destructive elements                         |
| `--border`               | `220 13% 88%`       | All borders, separators, input outlines              |
| `--input`                | `220 13% 88%`       | Input field borders (same as `--border`)             |
| `--ring`                 | `211 100% 35%`      | Focus ring (matches primary)                         |

### Color Rules
- **Never** use raw hex/rgb values in components. Always use the token classes (`text-primary`, `bg-destructive`, etc.).
- **Never** use generic red/blue/green. Use the curated palette above.
- Success messages use `bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-600 border-emerald-500/20`.
- Error messages use `bg-destructive/10 text-destructive border-destructive/20`.
- Role badges use `bg-primary/10 text-primary border-primary/20`.

---

## 3. Typography

### Font Families (CSS Custom Properties)
```
--font-display: "Merriweather", Georgia, serif;
--font-body:    "Inter", system-ui, sans-serif;
```

| Context                                      | Font              | Tailwind Class    |
|----------------------------------------------|-------------------|-------------------|
| Page titles (`<h1>`)                         | Merriweather      | `font-serif`      |
| Section headings (`<h2>`, `<h3>`)            | Merriweather      | `font-serif`      |
| Card titles, panel headers                   | Merriweather      | `font-serif`      |
| Body text, descriptions                      | Inter             | `font-sans` (default) |
| Form labels                                  | Inter             | `font-sans` (default) |
| Buttons, inputs, selects, badges, nav links  | Inter             | `font-sans` (default) |
| Arabic locale override                       | Cairo / Noto Naskh Arabic | automatic via `html[lang="ar"]` CSS |

### Size Conventions
| Element                      | Classes                                                |
|------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| Page Hero `<h1>`             | `text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold font-serif tracking-tight leading-tight` |
| Section `<h2>`               | `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold font-serif tracking-tight` |
| Panel/Card Header `<h3>`     | `font-serif font-bold text-lg text-foreground`         |
| Panel Description            | `text-xs text-muted-foreground`                        |
| Body text                    | `text-sm` (default) or `text-xs` for metadata          |
| Micro-labels (dates, tags)   | `text-[10px]`                                          |

---

## 4. Form System

### Labels
All form labels MUST use this exact class string:
```
text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground block
```
Alternate short-hand references: "micro-label" pattern. Never use `text-sm` or larger for form labels.

### Inputs
All `<input>`, `<textarea>`, and `<select>` elements MUST use:
```
w-full border border-border bg-background px-3 py-2.5 text-sm focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary focus:outline-none
```
- **No rounded corners** — the global `--radius: 0px` handles this automatically.
- Textareas add `min-h-[100px] resize-y`.

### Grid Layout (6-column)
Dashboard forms use a 6-column responsive grid:
```
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-6 gap-x-6 gap-y-5">
```

| Width Need                   | Col Span                   | Inputs Per Row |
|------------------------------|---------------------------|----------------|
| Standard field (name, email) | `col-span-1 md:col-span-3`| 2              |
| Narrow field (date, select)  | `col-span-1 md:col-span-2`| 3              |
| Full-width (bio, URL, textarea) | `col-span-1 md:col-span-6`| 1           |

### Checkboxes (multi-select, e.g. project members)
```
<label className="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm cursor-pointer hover:bg-secondary/30 p-1.5 transition-colors">
  <input type="checkbox" className="accent-primary" ... />
  <span>Member Name</span>
</label>
```

### Form Sections
Each form section starts with a `<Separator />` followed by a section micro-label:
```
<span className="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground block mb-1">
  Section Title
</span>
```

### Submit Buttons
- Primary action: `<Button>` (default variant) with `w-full md:w-auto` sizing.
- Destructive action: `variant="destructive"`.
- Cancel/Reset: `variant="outline"`.
- Always include a `gap-2` with a Lucide icon before the label.

---

