## 6. Page & Layout Patterns

### Global Page Wrapper
```jsx
<div className="pageWrapper">
  <a href="#main-content" className="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
  <Header />
  <NavBar />
  <Routes>...</Routes>
  <Footer />
</div>
```

### Container
All page content MUST be wrapped in:
```
<div className="container-custom">  <!-- max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 w-full -->
```

### Page Structure
Every page follows this pattern:
```jsx
<main id="main-content">
  <PageHero title="..." >
    {/* Breadcrumb links */}
    <Link to="/">Home</Link>
    <span aria-hidden="true" className="mx-1.5 select-none text-muted-foreground/60"> / </span>
    <span>Current Page</span>
  </PageHero>
  <section className="py-12 bg-background">
    <div className="container-custom">
      {/* Page content */}
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
```

### Dashboard Layout (Sidebar + Panel)
```
grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8 items-start
├── <aside>  (sidebar tabs, 1 col)
└── <div className="lg:col-span-3">  (main panel, 3 cols)
```

### Sidebar Tab Buttons
```
w-full text-left px-4 py-3 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider transition-all duration-150 flex items-center gap-3 border
```
- **Active state**: `bg-foreground text-background border-foreground shadow-sm`
- **Inactive state**: `text-muted-foreground hover:bg-secondary/50 hover:text-foreground border-transparent`

### Flash / Toast Notifications
Success and error messages appear at the top of the dashboard panel:
- **Success**: `bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-600 text-xs p-3.5 border border-emerald-500/20 font-medium`
- **Error**: `bg-destructive/10 text-destructive text-xs p-3.5 border border-destructive/20 font-medium`
- Auto-dismiss after 4 seconds via `setTimeout`.

---

## 7. NavBar & Navigation

### Desktop
- Sticky: `sticky top-0 z-40 w-full border-b border-border bg-background/95 backdrop-blur py-3`
- Uses Radix `NavigationMenu` with dropdown for team listings.
- Active link: `text-primary font-semibold`. Inactive: `text-muted-foreground`.

### Mobile
- Hamburger triggers a Radix `Sheet` (slide-in panel).
- Sheet side is RTL-aware: `side={isRtl ? "left" : "right"}`.
- Links close the sheet on click via `onClick={() => setMobileOpen(false)}`.

### Breadcrumbs
Always rendered inside `<PageHero>`:
```
<nav className="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-primary font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center gap-1.5 flex-wrap">
```
Separator: `<span aria-hidden="true" className="mx-1.5 select-none text-muted-foreground/60"> / </span>`

---

## 8. RTL & Multilingual Compatibility

### Languages Supported
| Code | Language | Direction |
|------|----------|-----------|
| `en` | English  | LTR       |
| `fr` | French   | LTR       |
| `ar` | Arabic   | RTL       |

### RTL Rules
1. `<html dir="rtl">` is set automatically by `LanguageContext` when `lang === 'ar'`.
2. Flex containers that need to reverse use the helper class `.flex-row-reverse-rtl:not(.grid)`.
3. **NEVER** combine `.grid` and `.flex-row-reverse-rtl` on the same element — it collapses column widths.
4. `SectionTitle` border accent flips: `border-l-4` → `rtl:border-r-4`.
5. Table cells use `rtl:text-right`.
6. Form text alignment uses `text-start` (not `text-left`) for RTL compatibility.

### Arabic Font Override
```css
html[lang="ar"] {
  --font-display: "Cairo", "Noto Naskh Arabic", serif;
  --font-body: "Cairo", "Noto Naskh Arabic", sans-serif;
}
```

### Translation
- All user-facing text goes through `useTranslation()` hook returning `t(key)` and `lang`.
- Translation files: `src/locales/en.json`, `src/locales/fr.json`, `src/locales/ar.json`.
- Fallback pattern: `t('key') || 'English fallback'`.
- Inline ternary for short labels: `lang === 'ar' ? 'عربي' : 'English'`.

---

## 9. Icons

Use **Lucide React** (`lucide-react`) exclusively. Never use FontAwesome, Heroicons, or emoji.

### Standard Icon Size
- Default: `h-4 w-4` (16px).
- Large (hero/empty states): `h-6 w-6`.
- Inside buttons: always pair with `gap-2` on the button.

### Commonly Used Icons
| Icon           | Usage                    |
|---------------|--------------------------|
| `User`        | Profile tab               |
| `BookOpen`    | Publications tab          |
| `Briefcase`   | Projects tab              |
| `Users`       | Members/Team tab          |
| `Megaphone`   | News/Announcements tab    |
| `Plus`        | Add/Create actions        |
| `Trash2`      | Delete actions            |
| `Calendar`    | Date display              |
| `LogOut`      | Logout button             |
| `Sparkles`    | Special features          |
| `Layers`      | Teams/Categories          |
| `Settings`    | Configuration             |
| `X`           | Close/dismiss             |
| `Menu`        | Mobile hamburger          |
| `ExternalLink`| External URL links        |

---

## 10. Confirmations & Dialogs

### CRITICAL RULE
**NEVER** use `window.confirm()` or `window.alert()`. Always use state-based Radix `<Dialog>` modals.

### Confirmation Dialog Pattern
```jsx
const [confirmDialog, setConfirmDialog] = useState({
  open: false,
  title: '',
  description: '',
  onConfirm: null
});

const requestConfirm = (title, description, onConfirmAction) => {
  setConfirmDialog({
    open: true,
    title,
    description,
    onConfirm: () => {
      onConfirmAction();
      setConfirmDialog(prev => ({ ...prev, open: false }));
    }
  });
};
```

### Dialog Styling
- Overlay: `bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-sm`
- Content: `border border-border bg-background p-6 shadow-lg`
- Title: `font-serif font-bold text-lg`
- Description: `text-sm text-muted-foreground`
- Footer buttons: confirm (primary/destructive) + cancel (outline)
- **No rounded corners** on dialog content panel.

---

## 11. Data Layer & State Management

### Context Providers (wrap the entire app)
```
<LanguageProvider>     → useLanguage() — lang, setLang
  <AuthProvider>       → useAuth() — user, login, logout, refreshUser
    <BrowserRouter>
```

### Database Service
`src/lib/dbService.js` — abstraction over localStorage mock database.
- All CRUD operations are `async` functions.
- Data is seeded on first load from `src/data/` JSON files.
- Translation-aware: many getters accept a `lang` parameter.

### Custom Hooks
| Hook               | File                         | Returns                                    |
|--------------------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| `useTranslation()` | `src/hooks/useTranslation.js`| `{ t, lang }`                               |
| `usePublications()`| `src/hooks/usePublications.js`| `{ publications, loading, getCitationText }`|
| `useTeams()`       | `src/hooks/useTeams.js`      | `{ teams, members }`                        |

